✅ Rate Limiting
Meaning: Setting a maximum number of requests allowed in a given time window.
📌 Example:
100 requests per minute per user
If user exceeds it → server blocks/rejects requests (usually 429 Too Many Requests).
Purpose: Protect APIs from abuse, spam, DDoS.

✅ Throttling
Meaning: Slowing down requests when the limit is reached instead of fully blocking immediately.
📌 Example:
After 100 requests/min, server starts responding slower or delays responses.
Purpose: Control traffic smoothly and prevent overload.


🔥 Key Difference
Rate limiting = stop/block after limit
Throttling = slow down after limit
Both are used for API protection and traffic control.